  "confidence": 0.85,
  "reasoning": "The HDA Intel driver implements recovery mechanisms for codec communication timeouts by setting polling_mode and single_cmd flags. However, these flags are never reset during suspend/resume cycles. After suspend/resume, the hardware is reset but the software flags remain set, causing the driver to continue using workaround modes (polling mode, single_cmd mode) even though the hardware should be able to communicate normally again with CORB/RIRB. This mismatch between hardware state and software flags causes repeated timeouts and choppy audio output. The polling_mode flag is set at line 912 and single_cmd at line 951 as recovery mechanisms, but there is no code path that resets them during suspend (azx_suspend, lines 2513-2537) or resume (azx_resume, lines 2539-2566, and azx_runtime_suspend, lines 2570-2578). The fix requires resetting polling_mode to 0 and single_cmd to its initial module parameter value during suspension or before reinitialization during resume."
}

